on run
	set theSubject to "SME reps for the LIMSOC 2026-27 priorities"
	set theBody to "Hey team,

Hope you're all keeping well. I've chatted to each of you about this separately, looking to pull it together now and get the SME reps sorted by early next week.

The four groups and the reps we'd like on each:

•    Incident Categorisation and Flow: LSV Comms, SDO, SAC, Reporting
•    Call Out Systems and Capabilities: LSV Comms, SDO, Ops Officer
•    Rostering within LIMSOC: Club captain reps (a couple, mix of remote/metro, large/small), Ops Officer
•    AI within our Incident Management Practice: LSV Comms, SDO, SAC, ARO

What do you think? Would like to have these in place by next week if we can. Open to suggestions on the best next steps from here.

Let me know.

Cheers,
Nick"

	tell application "Microsoft Outlook"
		activate
		set theMessage to make new outgoing message with properties {subject:theSubject, content:theBody}
		open theMessage
	end tell

	return "draft created: " & theSubject
end run
